9 H. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall
10 promulgate rules for the determination of student compliance with
11 agreements made pursuant to this section.
12 I. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall
13 designate personnel to coordinate tracking of program records for
14 the years when students participating in the program are still in
15 the schools or are being educated by other means, provide staff
16 development for contact persons in the schools, and provide liaison
17 with the State Board of Education and local organizations and
18 individuals participating in the program.
19 J. The school district where an Oklahoma Higher Learning Access
20 Program student is enrolled when the student begins participation in
21 the program and any subsequent school district where the student
22 enrolls shall forward information regarding participation by the
23 student in the program to a school to which the student transfers
24 upon the request of the school for the records of the student.
Req. No. 17190 Page 24

1 K. Students participating in the Oklahoma Higher Learning
2 Access Program shall provide their Social Security number or their
3 student identification number used by their school to the Oklahoma
4 State Regents for Higher Education. The State Regents shall keep
5 the numbers confidential and use them only for administrative
6 purposes.
7 L. The State Regents may provide an exception to the age limits
8 provided for in paragraphs 1 and 2 of subsection C of this section
9 to a student due to hardship circumstances and allow an application
10 to the Oklahoma Higher Learning Access Program for twelfth-grade
11 students enrolled in a public or private school and students who are
12 educated by other means and are in the equivalent of twelfth grade.
13 Provided, however, the exception due to hardship circumstances shall
14 not apply to:
15 1. A student enrolled in a public or private school after the
16 student's official date of high school graduation;
17 2. A student educated by other means who is age nineteen (19)
18 or older; or
19 3. Any student who is age twenty-one (21) or older.
20 The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall promulgate
21 rules to implement the provisions of this subsection.
